---
// §3 — Not-just-AI pivot. A single quiet beat that reframes the MCP server as
// one more way into a real wiki, not an AI gimmick stapled on.
---
<section class="pivot">
  <div class="section section--tight pivot-inner reveal-up">
    <p class="kicker"><span class="kicker-dot"></span>A real wiki first</p>
    <h2 class="pivot-title">
      A wiki on its own —<br />
      <span class="accent">with or without the AI.</span>
    </h2>
    <p class="pivot-body">
      Block editing, real-time collaboration, comments, version history, sharing — tela works as a
      wiki without any of the AI. The Claude and ChatGPT connector is one more way in, not the whole
      product.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .pivot { border-block: 1px solid var(--border); background: var(--surface-sunk); }
  .pivot-inner { text-align: left; }
  .pivot-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.25rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-display);
    line-height: var(--leading-tight);
    color: var(--fg);
    max-width: 26ch;
    text-wrap: balance;
  }
  .pivot-title .accent { color: var(--brand); }
  .pivot-body {
    margin-top: 1.4rem;
    max-width: var(--measure);
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    line-height: var(--leading-normal);
    color: var(--fg-soft);
  }
</style>
